      <h3 id="conference-and-workshop-papers">Conference and Workshop papers</h3>

<p><strong><font color="#0099CC">O Single Sign-Off, Where Art Thou? An Empirical Analysis of Single Sign-On Account Hijacking and Session Management on the Web</font></strong> <br />
Mohammad Ghasemisharif, Amrutha Ramesh, Stephen Checkoway, Chris Kanich, and <u>Jason Polakis</u> <br />
In Proceedings of the <a href="https://www.usenix.org/conference/usenixsecurity18/">27th USENIX Security Symposium</a><br />
August 2018, Baltimore, MD. <!--(Acceptance Rate: 19% [100/524])--> 
[<a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/~polakis/papers/sso-usenix18.pdf">PDF</a>,
<a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/~sso-study/">Data</a>,
<a href="https://www.cs.uic.edu/~polakis/bibtex/usenix2018.html">BibTex</a>]
<br />▷ Due to the major Facebook hack our work has received significant international media coverage: 
<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/02/technology/personaltech/facebook-log-in-hack.html">New York Times (a)</a>,
<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/02/technology/facebook-hack-other-sites.html">New York Times (b)</a>,
<a href="https://www.wired.com/story/facebook-hack-single-sign-on-data-exposed/">WIRED</a>,
<a href="https://money.cnn.com/2018/10/01/technology/facebook-hack-tinder-pinterest/index.html">CNN</a>,
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2018/oct/02/facebook-hack-compromised-accounts-tokens">The Guardian</a>,
<a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/facebook-s-security-flaws-exposed-more-facebook-here-s-what-n915321">NBC</a>,
<a href="https://www.theregister.co.uk/2018/10/03/facebook_thirdparty_apps/">The Register</a>,
<a href="https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/nicolenguyen/what-to-do-facebook-security-breach-access-tokens">BuzzFeed</a>,
<a href="https://threatpost.com/facebook-breach-sparks-concerns-around-third-party-app-website-security/137918/">ThreatPost</a>,
<a href="https://www.yahoo.com/news/most-recent-facebook-hack-way-worse-probably-realize-000039744.html">Yahoo</a>,
